datasets.name: bde867be
datasets.query:
select
  CASE
    WHEN valid_date = 'NOT VALID' THEN 1
    ELSE 0
  END as valid_policy,
  CASE
    WHEN reported_severity_check = 'Severity matches the report' THEN 1
    ELSE 0
  END as correct_severity_assessment,
  CASE
    WHEN valid_amount = 'claim value more than premium' THEN 1
    ELSE 0
  END as approve_claim_amount,
  claim_amount_total,
  claim_amount_injury,
  claim_amount_property,
  claim_amount_vehicle,
  incident_severity as reported_severity,
  -- severity as predicted_severity,
  reported_severity_check,
  valid_amount,
  valid_date,
  claim_no
from
  `main__build`.`dbdemos_fsi_smart_claims`.claim_insights

  -- WHERE claim_no=:claim_no

datasets.name: 91609f01
datasets.query:
select
  valid_amount,
  count(*) as ctr
FROM
  `main__build`.`dbdemos_fsi_smart_claims`.claim_insights
where
  to_date(claim_date) >= :start_date
  and to_date(claim_date) <= :end_date
group by
  valid_amount
order by
  valid_amount desc

datasets.name: d826e134
datasets.query:
select
  claim_no,
  claim_date,
  policy_no,
  CASE
    WHEN valid_date = 'NOT VALID' THEN 0
    ELSE 1
  END as valid_policy,
  CASE
    WHEN reported_severity_check = 'Severity matches the report' THEN 0
    ELSE 1
  END as correct_severity_assessment,
  CASE
    WHEN valid_amount = 'claim value more than premium' THEN 0
    ELSE 1
  END as approve_claim_amount,
  claim_amount_total,
  claim_amount_injury,
  claim_amount_property,
  claim_amount_vehicle,
  incident_severity as reported_severity,
  -- severity as predicted_severity,
  reported_severity_check,
  valid_amount,
  valid_date
from
  `main__build`.`dbdemos_fsi_smart_claims`.claim_insights;

datasets.name: 6ec9e508
datasets.query:
select
  claim_no,
  claim_amount_total,
  claim_amount_injury,
  claim_amount_property,
  claim_amount_vehicle,
  to_date(claim_date),
  incident_type,
  incident_severity,
  incident_date,
  collision_type,
  collision_number_of_vehicles_involved,
  driver_age,
  driver_insured_relationship,
  driver_license_issue_date,
  months_as_customer,
  number_of_witnesses,
  suspicious_activity
from
  `main__build`.`dbdemos_fsi_smart_claims`.claim_insights

--where  claim_no = '{{claim_number}}';

datasets.name: 9ef54712
datasets.query:
select
  CHASSIS_NO,
  claim_no,
  avg(high_speed) as speeding,
  CASE
    WHEN avg(high_speed) < 0.25 THEN 0
    ELSE 1
  END as speeding_more_than_25percent
from
  (
    select
      chassis_no,
      claim_no,
      claim_date,
      policy_no,
      CASE
        WHEN speed_check = 'High Speed' THEN 1
        WHEN speed_check = 'Normal Speed' THEN 0
        ELSE -1000
      END as high_speed,
      claim_amount_total,
      incident_severity as reported_severity
    from
      `main__build`.`dbdemos_fsi_smart_claims`.claim_insights
  ) a

-- where a.claim_no = "{{claim_number}}"
group by
  CHASSIS_NO,
  claim_no;

datasets.name: 077489da
datasets.query:
select
  count(*) as expired_policies
FROM
  `main__build`.`dbdemos_fsi_smart_claims`.claim_insights
where
  pol_expiry_date < claim_date
  and to_date(claim_date) >= :start_date
  and to_date(claim_date) <= :end_date;

datasets.name: d45268a4
datasets.query:
select
  count(suspicious_activity) as fraud
FROM
  `main__build`.`dbdemos_fsi_smart_claims`.claim_insights
where
  suspicious_activity = true
  and to_date(claim_date) >= :start_date
  and to_date(claim_date) <= :end_date;
